FBIS4-35613 "drnes106_p_94001" FBIS-NES-94-106 Daily Report 31 May 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Cease-Fire in Force in Western Sections of Kabul Cease-Fire in Force in Western Sections of Kabul LD3105173594 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 GMT 31 May 94 LD3105173594 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Pashto BFN [Text]In order to prevent the possibility of future clashes in the western sections of Kabul city, a peace delegation consisting of representatives from the Islamic State of Afghanistan and representative from the Hezb-e Wahdat-e Eslami of Afghanistan [Unity Party of Afghanistan] have decided to implement a total cease-fire as from today in the western sections of Kabul city. The commission supervising cease-fire is to control the cease-fire and make sure that the roads leading to the western sections of Kabul city are open. The agreement says that the transgressors will be questioned and punished. Quoting eye-witnesses, the Bakhtar Information Agency correspondent reports that the enforced cease-fire is being fully observed today and the roads leading to western section of Kabul are open to traffic and people. The people continue to commute unimpeded.
